This forum exists to share my ideas and drafts of my work for public comment and scrutiny. Call it peer review.

It also serves as a transparent way for those I cite to validate or disagree with my arguments.

Rationale: 

Much of the academic scholarship about #bitcoin comes from writers who do not demonstrate a deep understanding of #bitcoin and its community

Knowledge creation/circulation in #bitcoin typically happens outside traditional institutions of knowledge production

More and more scholars are writing about #bitcoin as it becomes more prevalent. I hope to offer a characterization of #bitcoin they can cite that reflects the views of the actual community who builds, uses, and advocates for it.

Vernacular Economics is a dissertation project that seeks to offer a grounded study of the #bitcoin movement and its culture

Why?
